postcontent:
ORIGINAL CASE3-13 ROUND MAGSBRIGHT NIGHT SIGHTSVERY GOOD CONDITIONLEM TRIGGER
The HK Law Enforcement Modification trigger system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull from first to last round fired) with a double-action hammer system.
Developed especially for a U.S. government agency, the Law Enforcement Modification (or LEM for short), is a unique trigger mechanism created specifically to improve the trigger performance and reduce the weight of the Double-Action Only (DAO) trigger pull on HK pistols.
With this mechanism, HK pistols can be fired like a standard DAO semi-automatic pistol where every round is fired by simply pulling the trigger fully rearward with the hammer starting at the forward rest position. The design of the proprietary HK LEM system allows the weight of the DAO trigger pull to be reduced to a smooth and constant 6.18 - 8.5 pounds (27.5 - 37.8 N) because the two-part hammer is pre-cocked every time the slide moves rearward. Trigger pull on conventional double action pistols is 12 - 15 pounds (53.4 - 66.7N).
The unique LEM pre-cocked hammer system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull and short trigger travel from first to last round fired) with a double action hammer system. Optional adjustment (by HK certified armorer) can bring the trigger pull into the 5.5 pound (24.5 N) range.
Using such an enhanced trigger system consolidates ease of use and safety into a convenient, innovative trigger operation �?" one that prevents unintended firing. And in case of an ammunition-related failure to fire, all that is needed is an additional second or third pull of the trigger without the need of first pulling the slide back to re-cock the P2000. The enhanced LEM trigger system combines the reliability of a double action revolver trigger with the crisp, precise trigger of a single action pistol.

title: For Sale:  Yugoslavian M48, Bolt Active Surplus, Great Condition
postcontent: For sale is a Yugoslavian M48. These are bolt action military surplus rifles chambered in the robust 8mm Mauser cartridge. This particular one is in excellent condition, clean bore, all matching parts and original stock with no cracks. Yugoslavian Crest is present and proud on the receiver.The M48 was developed by Yugoslavia after WW2 and were essentially the final evolution of military mauser rifles such as the German k98. title: For Sale:  Czech vz. 24 WW2 Rifle + Bayonet
postcontent: For sale is a Czech vz.24. These were the Czech flavor of the WW2 bolt action combat rifle. It is chambered in 8mm Mauser and includes the historical bayonet. All metal parts of the rifle including the bayonet are black coated steel.The Czech vz.24 was produced in Brno, Czechslovakia ramping up to WW2. When Czechslovakia was annexed by Germany in 1938 production continued for a while before the plant was eventually converted to producing the similar, but coincidently more German, k98.Judging from the serial number it is likely this particular rifle was produced not long before annexation. Like most things in the region it eventually was captured by the Soviet army who then re-matched parts and electrostenciled their own serial to the bolt. Eventually it made its way out of siezed stock and found their way to the US. Despite what seems to have been quite the journey the current rifle is in great condition with a clean shiny bore. Stock looks great and is not cracked, but looks like it may have been fixed up somewhat by the military arsenals.This rifle has character, but still well built and shoots accurately. This is a great rifle to own for history, hunting, plinking, or collection.
